018package org.opengis.filter;
019
020import org.opengis.annotation.UML;
021
022import static org.opengis.annotation.Specification.ISO_19143;
023
024
025/**
026 * Thrown if {@code SortBy} has multiple {@code SortProperty} elements referencing the same value.
027 *
028 * @author  Martin Desruisseaux (Geomatys)
029 * @version 3.1
030 * @since   3.1
031 */
032@UML(identifier="DuplicateSortKey", specification=ISO_19143)
033public class DuplicateSortKeyException extends RuntimeException {
034    /**
035     * Serial number for inter-operability with different versions.
036     */
037    private static final long serialVersionUID = -5514345183414858878L;
038
039    /**
040     * Creates an exception with no message.
041     */
042    public DuplicateSortKeyException() {
043        super();
044    }
045
046    /**
047     * Creates an exception with the specified message.
048     *
049     * @param message  the detail message, saved for later retrieval by the {@link #getMessage()} method.
050     */
051    public DuplicateSortKeyException(final String message) {
052        super(message);
053    }
054
055    /**
056     * Creates an exception with the specified message and cause.
057     *
058     * @param message  the detail message, saved for later retrieval by the {@link #getMessage()} method.
059     * @param cause    the cause, saved for later retrieval by the {@link #getCause()} method.
060     */
061    public DuplicateSortKeyException(final String message, final Throwable cause) {
062        super(message, cause);
063    }
064}
